<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-ellipsis" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Words Omitted by Editor for Brevity</head>
    <p>Word or words omitted for the sake of brevity or emphasis by the editor while discussing or
        quoting a text.</p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="gap"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>

    <p>The omitted words should be placed inside a <gi>gap</gi> element whose <att>reason</att>
        attribute should have a value of "ellipsis".</p>

    <cit>
        <quote>... or [...]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>XI.4</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="ellipsis"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london"
        corresp="http://inslib.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT738.html">
        <gap reason="ellipsis"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="ddbdp"
        corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;2;459#1">
        <gap reason="ellipsis" quantity="1" unit="line">
            <desc>Demotic</desc>
        </gap>
    </egXML>

    <divGen type="seealso"/>

    <div xml:id="trans-ellipsis-responsibility">

        <head>Responsibility for this section</head>
        <listBibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                    <resp>author</resp>
                    <name>Scott Vanderbilt</name>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt></bibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                    <resp>author</resp>
                    <name>Charlotte Tupman</name>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt></bibl>
        </listBibl>
    </div>
</div>
